Using Google Earth Engine (GEE) is a fantastic, bulletproof workaround. It bypasses NASA's API limitations and package bugs entirely. 

By running a simple script in the GEE Code Editor, you can export the exact cropped 2023 Ghana nighttime lights raster directly to your Google Drive in less than 2 minutes.

---

### 🛰️ Step 1: Export the Raster from Earth Engine
1. Open your browser and go to the **[Google Earth Engine Code Editor](https://code.earthengine.google.com/)** (log in with any Google account).
2. Copy and paste the following JavaScript code into the main editor window:

```javascript
// 1. Get the Ghana boundary
var ghana = ee.FeatureCollection("USDOS/LSIB_SIMPLE/2017")
  .filter(ee.Filter.eq("country_na", "Ghana"));

// 2. Load NOAA VIIRS Monthly Nighttime Lights (2023)
var viirs = ee.ImageCollection("NOAA/VIIRS/DNB/MONTHLY_V1/VCMSLCFG")
  .filterDate('2023-01-01', '2023-12-31')
  .select('avg_rad')
  .median() // Take the median to remove clouds and ephemeral background noise
